00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:54,987
narrator: coconut shells used to be considered     

4
00:00:54,989 --> 00:00:56,721
agricultural waste,      

5
00:00:56,723 --> 00:01:00,659
but today they're processed into biofuel for the barbecue. 

6
00:01:00,661 --> 00:01:02,394
in countries like thailand,  

7
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,930
companies convert the shells into briquettes        

8
00:01:04,932 --> 00:01:07,666
that burn cleanly for an extended period.    

9
00:01:07,668 --> 00:01:11,437
throwing away these shells   
would be a real waste of energy.

10
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:16,075
instead of ending up as landfill,          

11
00:01:16,077 --> 00:01:19,744
coconut shells are being used to fire the grill.    

12
00:01:19,746 --> 00:01:23,215
processed into briquettes that burn virtually smoke-free,   

13
00:01:23,217 --> 00:01:28,286
the shells are now considered a resource instead of garbage. 

14
00:01:28,288 --> 00:01:31,156
converting coconut shells to charcoal starts       

15
00:01:31,158 --> 00:01:34,259
with the partial-combustion process.            

16
00:01:34,261 --> 00:01:36,962
inside these brick igloo-style kilns,       

17
00:01:36,964 --> 00:01:38,697
they create a burning environment     

18
00:01:38,699 --> 00:01:40,899
that allows the shells to be carbonized        

19
00:01:40,901 --> 00:01:44,636
but doesn't reduce them to ash.      

20
00:01:44,638 --> 00:01:47,572
the kilns are partially underground.     

21
00:01:47,574 --> 00:01:50,642
the surrounding soil helps to seal the fire.       

22
00:01:50,644 --> 00:01:56,448
this keeps the air levels down for a slow, smoldering burn.  

23
00:01:56,450 --> 00:02:00,586
a worker bricks up the kiln door.         

24
00:02:00,588 --> 00:02:04,055
and he seals these bricks with mud instead of cement.  

25
00:02:04,057 --> 00:02:06,658
this will allow the door to be dismantled later     

26
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:08,259
without ruining the bricks,  

27
00:02:08,261 --> 00:02:11,263
preserving them for reuse in the next burn.       

28
00:02:15,602 --> 00:02:18,470
from the top, he ignites the fire using soft      

29
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:20,472
wax as starter material.    

30
00:02:25,946 --> 00:02:28,547
because of the limited air in the kilns,         

31
00:02:28,549 --> 00:02:33,285
the fire burns out after 20 to 24 hours.     

32
00:02:33,287 --> 00:02:36,488
a worker takes the door apart and rakes the charred remains 

33
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:39,291
of the coconut shells into a basket.         

34
00:02:42,229 --> 00:02:46,898
they have been converted into a rich charcoal.     

35
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,735
he heaps the blackened shells into a pile.      

36
00:02:54,775 --> 00:02:57,775
and under the intense sun, moisture from water,      

37
00:02:57,777 --> 00:03:02,580
used to extinguish any hot spots, evaporates.   

38
00:03:02,582 --> 00:03:06,384
the charcoal dries out and breaks easily.       

39
00:03:06,386 --> 00:03:09,621
it's now ready to be processed into briquettes.   

40
00:03:12,193 --> 00:03:15,627
workers load the charcoal pieces into grinders.     

41
00:03:18,332 --> 00:03:19,531
this is dirty work.      

42
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:22,000
so they protect their faces with scarves    

43
00:03:22,002 --> 00:03:25,403
and their hands with gloves.  

44
00:03:25,405 --> 00:03:27,272
inside the grinding machines, 

45
00:03:27,274 --> 00:03:29,808
rollers pulverize the charcoal,

46
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:32,277
reducing it to a fine powder. 

47
00:03:32,279 --> 00:03:36,281
the powder flows into bins below.        

48
00:03:36,283 --> 00:03:41,353
a worker then transfers the charcoal powder to a mixer.

49
00:03:41,355 --> 00:03:43,554
he adds a generous amount of starch made         

50
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:47,693
from the root of the cassava tree.      

51
00:03:47,695 --> 00:03:50,161
together with water, the starch will bond      

52
00:03:50,163 --> 00:03:54,233
the charcoal particles together like glue.      

53
00:03:54,235 --> 00:03:58,570
the mixer whisks it all together like pastry.   

54
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:02,640
the consistency is right when the particles form clumps 

55
00:04:02,642 --> 00:04:06,311
when pressed together.     

56
00:04:06,313 --> 00:04:11,316
the moistened blend exits   
the mixer and spills into a bin.

57
00:04:13,921 --> 00:04:15,654
this coconut shell charcoal  

58
00:04:15,656 --> 00:04:18,457
is now ready to be pressed into briquettes.    

59
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:29,067
the next worker loads the charcoal into a press.   

60
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:32,203
it forces the tacky black powder through a die   

61
00:04:32,205 --> 00:04:34,673
to press it into a perpetual hexagon      

62
00:04:34,675 --> 00:04:36,675
with a hole in the center.   

63
00:04:41,481 --> 00:04:43,948
as the machine extrudes the charcoal,         

64
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,817
a worker chops it into briquettes       

65
00:04:45,819 --> 00:04:48,253
that are just over 3 inches in length.      

66
00:04:51,425 --> 00:04:53,291
these coconut charcoal briquettes      

67
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,692
have now taken shape.     

68
00:04:54,694 --> 00:04:57,062
but they're not yet ready for the grill.      

69
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:03,835
they're soft and mushy     
to the touch and crumble easily.

70
00:05:08,509 --> 00:05:09,708
to firm them up,        

71
00:05:09,710 --> 00:05:11,109
they place them in structures 

72
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:13,145
with open fires in the center. 

73
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,449
they close the doors      

74
00:05:17,451 --> 00:05:18,983
and leave the briquettes to bake

75
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:21,987
over a period of about 24 hours.

76
00:05:25,058 --> 00:05:28,260
the heat fuses         
the charcoal particles together.

77
00:05:28,262 --> 00:05:31,530
and the briquettes harden.   

78
00:05:31,532 --> 00:05:32,931
out of the curing chamber,   

79
00:05:32,933 --> 00:05:36,334
this briquette is solid to the touch and clean too.  

80
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:40,138
it leaves no sooty residue.  

81
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:43,008
from coconut shells to barbecue briquettes,    

82
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:46,945
it's been quite a transformation.       

83
00:05:46,947 --> 00:05:51,516
this coconut shell charcoal is now ready to sizzle.    

84
00:05:58,825 --> 00:06:00,892
♪♪         

