00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:07,632
narrator: in many disciplines, you have to take measurements. 

86
00:06:07,634 --> 00:06:10,034
sometimes, those measurements are so minute         

87
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:13,772
they're difficult or impossible
for the human eye to determine.

88
00:06:13,774 --> 00:06:16,441
so a ruler or tape measure can't help.      

89
00:06:16,443 --> 00:06:19,311
what you need instead is a precision-measuring tool 

90
00:06:19,313 --> 00:06:21,279
called a dial indicator.    

91
00:06:24,918 --> 00:06:26,385
on this dial indicator,    

92
00:06:26,387 --> 00:06:31,523
each graduation is 0.001 inches.        

93
00:06:31,525 --> 00:06:33,658
a full revolution of the hand measures      

94
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:36,795
100 thousandths of an inch.  

95
00:06:36,797 --> 00:06:39,397
to make a key component, called the bridge plate,    

96
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:42,467
this automated punch press stamps out brass circles,   

97
00:06:42,469 --> 00:06:46,338
which are about 2 inches in diameter.     

98
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:48,206
workers place each bridge plate

99
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:49,741
into a manual punch press,   

100
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:51,609
which makes location holes   

101
00:06:51,611 --> 00:06:53,478
that will correctly position the bridge plate        

102
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:56,080
on the next press.       

103
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:58,550
this press makes holes for mounting screws,      

104
00:06:58,552 --> 00:07:02,154
locating pins, as well as for three precision jewels, 

105
00:07:02,156 --> 00:07:05,957
which reduce friction on moving metal components.  

106
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:10,161
this lathe begins the process 
of shaping a stainless steel rod

107
00:07:10,163 --> 00:07:12,964
into the dial indicator's main measuring component,   

108
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:15,366
called the rack.        

109
00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:17,168
under a shower of cutting oil,        

110
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:19,971
the machine drills and threads a hole on each end       

111
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:22,974
for attaching a contact made of plated steel.     

112
00:07:25,378 --> 00:07:28,380
next, this milling machine cuts teeth spaced       

113
00:07:28,382 --> 00:07:31,917
25 thousandths of an inch apart.       

114
00:07:31,919 --> 00:07:34,186
one of the dial indicator's gears runs     

115
00:07:34,188 --> 00:07:36,455
along these rack teeth to turn the hand        

116
00:07:36,457 --> 00:07:40,057
that displays the measurement.        

117
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:43,128
this computer-guided machine forms an aluminum bar     

118
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:44,529
into another key component,  

119
00:07:44,531 --> 00:07:45,797
called the bridge.       

120
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:48,800
the bridge has holes for screws

121
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,067
and locating pins       

122
00:07:50,069 --> 00:07:52,136
that align with those in the bridge plate      

123
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:53,938
so that the two can fasten,  

124
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:57,275
sandwiching the gears in between.          

125
00:07:57,277 --> 00:08:00,077
the bridge also has holes for three jewels,       

126
00:08:00,079 --> 00:08:03,148
which workers insert with a punch press.      

127
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:05,884
jewels are doughnut-shaped synthetic rubies        

128
00:08:05,886 --> 00:08:08,153
set in a brass ring.      

129
00:08:08,155 --> 00:08:09,688
they line the holes for the gears         

130
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:11,690
and other moving components.  

131
00:08:11,692 --> 00:08:13,558
the jewel's surface is very smooth.        

132
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:17,362
so it eases friction on the component.       

133
00:08:17,364 --> 00:08:20,298
workers check every jewel under a microscope       

134
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:24,035
to make sure it didn't crack when pressed into the hole.  

135
00:08:24,037 --> 00:08:27,372
the dial indicator's outside case is made of aluminum,   

136
00:08:27,374 --> 00:08:30,909
shaped by this computer-guided turning and milling machine.  

137
00:08:33,313 --> 00:08:35,980
workers spray the case with powdered paint      

138
00:08:35,982 --> 00:08:37,315
using an electric charge    

139
00:08:37,317 --> 00:08:39,584
to draw the particles onto the surface        

140
00:08:39,586 --> 00:08:43,188
in a thorough, even coat.   

141
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:46,124
then, they bake the case in an oven for 20 minutes   

142
00:08:46,126 --> 00:08:48,593
to make the paint finish ultra durable.     

143
00:08:51,131 --> 00:08:52,864
they put the case on a machine 

144
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:55,333
that presses in top and bottom steel stems,  

145
00:08:55,335 --> 00:08:57,636
which will hold the rack in place.       

146
00:09:05,412 --> 00:09:09,147
they mount a hair spring on the bridge plate.      

147
00:09:09,149 --> 00:09:11,016
this spring allows the gear  

148
00:09:11,018 --> 00:09:13,284
to return to its original position       

149
00:09:13,286 --> 00:09:16,121
after moving the rack upward to take a measurement.     

150
00:09:20,027 --> 00:09:21,760
they insert what's called a pinion        

151
00:09:21,762 --> 00:09:25,296
for the large dial hand in the center jeweled hole   

152
00:09:25,298 --> 00:09:27,098
and a second gear into the jeweled hole     

153
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:30,035
for the small dial hand.    

154
00:09:30,037 --> 00:09:33,304
then, they attach the bridge. 

155
00:09:33,306 --> 00:09:35,907
next, they insert the rack   

156
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:37,909
into the case through the stem 

157
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:42,380
and screw a contact into each end.         

158
00:09:42,382 --> 00:09:45,783
then, they install a brass spring-loaded rack guide.   

159
00:09:45,785 --> 00:09:47,585
it prevents the rack from rotating     

160
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:51,789
so that its teeth always face the rack gear.   

161
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:54,125
they mate the case with the rest.         

162
00:09:54,127 --> 00:09:55,994
then they push in the stem   

163
00:09:55,996 --> 00:10:00,532
while holding the hand pinion to wind the gear.       

164
00:10:00,534 --> 00:10:02,600
they install the printed aluminum dial   

165
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,468
on the bridge plate side    

166
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:07,405
and mount the hand for the small dial on a pinion   

167
00:10:07,407 --> 00:10:11,409
protruding from the top of the gear.          

168
00:10:11,411 --> 00:10:14,446
they mount the large dial hand onto its pinion.     

169
00:10:17,084 --> 00:10:18,749
they place the movable dial  

170
00:10:18,751 --> 00:10:20,885
into a grooved ring, called a bezel,        

171
00:10:20,887 --> 00:10:23,621
and snap the bezel onto the case.         

172
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:27,425
when you turn the bezel, the dial moves with it.    

173
00:10:27,427 --> 00:10:29,561
the back of the case is shaped with a lug      

174
00:10:29,563 --> 00:10:33,565
for mounting the tool to a fixture.         

175
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:37,034
the movable dial lets you zero the indicator.  

176
00:10:37,036 --> 00:10:40,105
you lock in the dial position with this twist bolt.     

177
00:10:43,577 --> 00:10:45,710
the factory tests every dial indicator      

178
00:10:45,712 --> 00:10:47,912
with this micrometer head.   

179
00:10:47,914 --> 00:10:51,783
it pushes in the rack to a specific measurement.   

180
00:10:51,785 --> 00:10:54,919
every time the large hand rotates a full revolution,   

181
00:10:54,921 --> 00:10:57,522
indicating 100 thousandths of an inch,    

182
00:10:57,524 --> 00:11:01,592
the small dial hand clocks one graduation.        

183
00:11:01,594 --> 00:11:05,129
this test guarantees no tool leaves the factory   

184
00:11:05,131 --> 00:11:08,133
without delivering made-to-measure accuracy.   

185
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,672
♪♪         

186
00:11:17,144 --> 00:11:19,677
narrator: cutting or sanding metals and other materials   

187
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:22,947
can produce combustible airborne dust or fumes,    

188
00:11:22,949 --> 00:11:25,283
which can ignite or be inhaled.

189
00:11:25,285 --> 00:11:27,418
that's why it's safer to do this work        

190
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:29,754
on a wet downdraft table.   

191
00:11:29,756 --> 00:11:32,823
this machine captures and filters hazardous particles

192
00:11:32,825 --> 00:11:36,961
from the work space.      

193
00:11:36,963 --> 00:11:40,231
a powerful blower pulls the flammable dust down    

194
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,166
through the openings of the grid tabletop.     

195
00:11:42,168 --> 00:11:46,504
then a continuous spray of water
extinguishes the dust     

196
00:11:46,506 --> 00:11:49,374
and washes it down into a reservoir at the bottom,   

197
00:11:49,376 --> 00:11:51,576
where a filter removes it.   

198
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:54,646
because stainless steel doesn't corrode,        

199
00:11:54,648 --> 00:11:57,382
this computer-guided laser cuts the components   

200
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:59,450
that come into contact with water           

201
00:11:59,452 --> 00:12:01,386
out of stainless steel sheets. 

202
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:09,060
workers pass each part through a wide-belt sander       

203
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:12,030
to smooth out rough edges left by the cutting.      

204
00:12:17,937 --> 00:12:20,071
when the part exits the sander,

205
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:22,974
they thoroughly brush off the metal dust.        

206
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:30,081
then, they bend the part into the required shape    

207
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:31,816
using a computer-guided machine,

208
00:12:31,818 --> 00:12:34,285
called a press brake.     

209
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:43,628
a welder then fuses the parts, 

210
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:47,565
constructing the machine in sections.          

211
00:12:47,567 --> 00:12:50,901
this is the table section that contains the tabletop   

212
00:12:50,903 --> 00:12:52,103
and the wash-down system    

213
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:56,574
that processes the combustible dust.     

214
00:12:56,576 --> 00:12:58,843
workers clean all the welds with a machine         

215
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:02,847
that uses a combination of chemicals and electricity. 

216
00:13:02,849 --> 00:13:04,649
they brush on a protective coating      

217
00:13:04,651 --> 00:13:08,520
to make the welds corrosion-resistant.      

218
00:13:08,522 --> 00:13:11,456
then, they wash the unit with soap and water.      

219
00:13:13,893 --> 00:13:15,459
in the reservoir at the bottom,

220
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:18,062
they install the water-inlet filter.    

221
00:13:18,064 --> 00:13:20,865
when the blower sucks the dust under the tabletop,  

222
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:24,001
spray nozzles douse it with water.          

223
00:13:24,003 --> 00:13:26,871
the dusty water flows down into the reservoir,      

224
00:13:26,873 --> 00:13:28,873
where this filter traps the dust

225
00:13:28,875 --> 00:13:34,411
before a pump sends the water back up to the spray nozzles. 

226
00:13:34,413 --> 00:13:36,815
to ensure that no water leaks out,      

227
00:13:36,817 --> 00:13:39,617
a worker caulks this entire section of the machine     

228
00:13:39,619 --> 00:13:41,553
with marine-grade sealant.   

229
00:13:43,623 --> 00:13:45,756
on the left side, they mount the housing     

230
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:48,493
for the mist-eliminator filter.

231
00:13:48,495 --> 00:13:51,029
it captures water droplets from the airstream       

232
00:13:51,031 --> 00:13:53,231
before the blower exhausts it. 

233
00:13:55,368 --> 00:13:58,369
to that, they attach the blower housing.      

234
00:13:58,371 --> 00:14:00,305
it has a side opening for the blower         

235
00:14:00,307 --> 00:14:02,240
and a top opening for a silencer

236
00:14:02,242 --> 00:14:05,109
that muffles the noise of the blower exhaust.     

237
00:14:08,782 --> 00:14:10,982
now, they install the blower. 

238
00:14:10,984 --> 00:14:12,584
it consists of an electric motor      

239
00:14:12,586 --> 00:14:14,785
turning a blower wheel.    

240
00:14:14,787 --> 00:14:18,722
the resulting centrifugal force
sucks air through the machine 

241
00:14:18,724 --> 00:14:21,859
and out the exhaust.      

242
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:24,262
they insert the filter into its housing.       

243
00:14:24,264 --> 00:14:27,932
the filter is polyester, so it's mold resistant,    

244
00:14:27,934 --> 00:14:32,136
which is critical given that it gets wet.       

245
00:14:32,138 --> 00:14:34,205
now, they install the water tree,        

246
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:36,540
a stainless steel wall with baffles       

247
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:40,011
that make the dusty water cascade into the reservoir.  

248
00:14:42,815 --> 00:14:45,883
these probes ensure there's always the optimum amount   

249
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:49,286
of water circulating through the machine.      

250
00:14:49,288 --> 00:14:51,756
they send an alert to the control panel      

251
00:14:51,758 --> 00:14:53,491
if the water level in the reservoir        

252
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:56,327
rises too high or drops too low.       

253
00:14:58,764 --> 00:15:00,498
after installing a plumbing connection     

254
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,100
for the wash-down system,   

255
00:15:02,102 --> 00:15:03,968
they install walls to contain 

256
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:07,972
the dust over the work surface 

257
00:15:07,974 --> 00:15:12,710
and the silencer over the blower exhaust.    

258
00:15:12,712 --> 00:15:15,580
then, they complete the assembly
of the wash-down system    

259
00:15:15,582 --> 00:15:17,181
by connecting pipes with spray 

260
00:15:17,183 --> 00:15:20,652
nozzles to the plumbing connection.          

261
00:15:20,654 --> 00:15:23,788
finally, workers install the tabletop,     

262
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,390
made up of two steel grates.  

263
00:15:26,392 --> 00:15:30,260
the blower sucks the dust through the grates' openings. 

264
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:34,932
you can cushion the tabletop with a rubber grid mat.    

265
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:37,535
when you press the start button on the control panel,  

266
00:15:37,537 --> 00:15:39,870
the blower begins drawing air.          

